column2: Key Tronic Corp. engages in the provision of electronics manufacturing services. The company is headquartered in Spokane Valley, Washington and currently employs 4,067 full-time employees. The firm provides electronic manufacturing services (EMS) and solutions to original equipment manufacturers (OEMs) of a range of products. The firm provides engineering services, procurement and distribution, materials management, manufacturing and assembly services, in-house testing, and customer service. The firm provides EMS services, such as product design, surface mount technologies (SMT) and pin through hole capability for printed circuit board assembly (PCBA), tool making, precision plastic molding, sheet metal fabrication, liquid injection molding, complex assembly, automated tape winding, prototype design and full product assembly. The firm's manufacturing operations are located in Oakdale, Minnesota; Fayetteville, Arkansas; Corinth, Mississippi; Harrodsburg, Kentucky, and foreign manufacturing operations in Juarez, Mexico, and Shanghai, China.
